5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to public corruption convictions; to amend
10 Section 36-27D-1, Code of Alabama 1975, to use retirement
11 contributions made by a public servant found guilty of a
12 criminal offense involving his or her government position to
13 be used for restitution; to require a public servant to pay
14 back compensation received while on leave with pay in certain
15 circumstances; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions
16 to update the existing code language to current style.
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
