78 Section 2. (a)(1) Any public official or employee of
79 the state or a political subdivision thereof who is under any
80 investigation for committing a felony offense related to or
81 arising out of, or in connection with, the public official's
82 or employee's service in his or her public position may use,
83 if otherwise authorized by law, public funds to defend himself
84 or herself unless and until the public official or employee is
Page 3

or herself unless and until the public official or employee is
SB58 Engrossed
85 indicted for that felony offense.
86 (2) If the public official or employee is indicted for
87 the felony offense, the public official or employee may not
88 use any public funds to pay for his or her legal defense.
89 (b) Any public official or employee described in
90 subsection (a) who is placed on leave with pay while under
91 investigation, upon conviction for that felony offense, shall
92 be required to pay back all compensation received since the
93 commission of the felony offense.
94 Section 3. This act shall become effective on October
95 1, 2026.
